# CareerKundi project governance

- Read `AGENTS.md` and the approved prototype governance documents before substantive work.
- Treat repository code and accepted evidence as current truth.
- Treat `docs/prototype/approved/careerkundi_complete_interface_v1/` as approved target UX.
- Never infer an implemented backend, route, worker, integration or persistence operation from an image.
- Use the state vocabulary: `EVIDENCE_BACKED_CURRENT`, `UNVERIFIED_CURRENT`, `APPROVED_DESIGN_TARGET`, `PROPOSED_TARGET`, `CREATE_REQUIRED`.
- Before editing, identify the current phase, named gate, relevant Pxx/Pxx-A4-xx references and exact intended delta.
- Implement one approved slice at a time.
- Preserve unrelated work and known local dirt.
- Stage exact files only.
- Do not commit or push unless explicitly authorised.
- Stop at the named gate and produce evidence.
